                    <head>Polish Refugees of Zurich</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bendlikon, near Zurich</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 2, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>We, the emigrants from Poland, participate in the feeling of horror
                        experienced by all nations at the death of Mr. Lincoln, President of the
                        United States, who deserved well of humanity. Received with hospitality upon
                        the soil of Switzerland, we join our voices with the Helvetians in
                        expressions of condolence with the American people, and with their wishes
                        that the country where Pulaski and Kosciusko fought with Washington may be
                        strengthened in its independence and integrity by the absolute abolition of
                        slavery, clemency towards the conquered, equality of all its inhabitants,
                        and respect for the liberty of other nations.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">Managers and printers of the “Polish paper called the
                            Ojczyzna:</hi>
                    </p>
